DIFFRENCE BETWEEN GIT PULL AND GIT MERGE
purpose
   - git pull -> combines " git fetch " and  " git merge " updates local branch with changes from remote.
   - git merge ->  merges changes from one local branch to another.

workflow
   - git pull -> fetches updates, then merges. Conflicts must be resolved.
   - git merge -> combines branches locally without fetching.

usage scenarios
   - git pull -> for syncing with remote branches.
   - git merge -> for integrating feature branches into main branches.

result
   - git pull -> local branch is updated with remote changes.
   - git merge -> combines changes or create a merge commit." 
